caption.title: Representative cross-sectional view of the right femur during the early fetal period on 7-T MR image.
caption.p: The crown–rump length (CRL) of each fetus is indicated below the images. Yellow arrow: phase 4; red arrow: phase 5 according to Streeter’s classification. The region between the yellow arrows at the diaphysis corresponds to phase OS. The region outside the yellow arrows corresponds to phases 1–3.
